---
title: Thai Green Curry
description: Traditional Thai curry with aromatic spices, coconut milk, and fresh herbs.
---

Heat @coconut-milk{400%ml} in a large pan over medium heat.

Stir in @green-curry-paste{2%tbsp} and cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes.

Add @chicken-breast{500%g} sliced into bite-sized pieces and simmer until cooked through, about 8-10 minutes.

Add @thai-eggplant{200%g} and @green-beans{100%g}, simmering until vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.

Season with @fish-sauce{1%tbsp} and @palm-sugar{1%tbsp} to taste.

Squeeze fresh @lime{1} juice over the curry and stir in fresh @basil{1%bunch} leaves just before serving.
